In a #medium pot{}, combine @water{4%cups} and @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add onion; cook, stirring, until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add garlic, @Arborio Rice{3/4%cup}, and @Butter{1/2%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until garlic is fragrant and rice is translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add 1/2 cup stock to pan with rice mixture; stir until liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat with remaining stock—adding 1/2 cup at a time and stirring until liquid has mostly absorbed—until rice is al dente and mixture is creamy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need a little more or a little less liquid for the risotto.

Meanwhile, halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce}.

While risotto cooks, pat @Barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add barramundi, skin sides down. Cook until skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Cover to keep warm.

Once risotto is done, stir in mushrooms, tomatoes, @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon}, half the @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}, and half the chives (save the remaining Parmesan and chives for serving). Cook until tomatoes are softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If risotto is too thick, stir in another splash of water or stock.

Turn off heat. Stir in a pinch of @?Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired.

Divide risotto between #bowls{}. Top with remaining chives and remaining Parmesan. Sprinkle with a pinch of chili flakes to taste. Serve.

Top risotto with barramundi.